text: In Germany , influenza sentinel surveillance on outpatients of all ages [ 17 ] confirmed that the first postpandemic season 2010 / 11 was dominated by influenza A ( H1N1 ) pdm09 ( 62 % ) , co - circulating with influenza B ( 37 % ) whereas A ( H3N2 ) was rare ( < 1 % ) . During the second season 2011 / 12 , A ( H1N1 ) pdm09 was rare ( 1 % ) , whereas A ( H3N2 ) was diagnosed in 75 % of cases and co - circulated with influenza B ( 24 % ) . In the third season 2012 / 13 , all three types / subtypes co - circulated in similar proportions ( 34 % A ( H1N1 ) pdm2009 , 31 % A ( H3N2 ) , and 35 % B ) .
